@startuml
title Boomaga-IPP — Print/Preview/Submit Sequence (conforms to code @ 34652fa)
actor "Printer User" as User
participant "Host CUPS" as CUPS
participant "IppServer\n(boomaga-ipp-backend)" as IPP
participant "JobProcessor" as PROC
participant "JobQueue" as Q
participant "boomaga-ipc\n(Unix socket + JSON)" as IPC
participant "Xilem GUI\n(boomaga-preview)" as GUI
participant "DocumentRenderer\n(+poppler)" as REN
participant "boomaga-layout-engine" as LAY
participant "Downstream CUPS printer" as TARGET

== Capture (IPP Everywhere print service — realized) ==
User -> CUPS : print document
CUPS -> IPP  : IPP Create-Job / Send-Document (driverless)
IPP -> PROC  : add_job(PrintJobRequest)
PROC -> Q    : push(request)
Q --> PROC   : pop() -> PrintJobRequest

== Notify GUI (Unix-socket IPC — decided, NOT yet wired) ==
IPP -[#gray]->> IPC : <<planned>> Message{ PrintJobRequest }
IPC -[#gray]->> GUI : <<planned>> job available

== Preview (renderer present; poppler integration in progress) ==
GUI -> REN : load(path)
REN --> GUI : Document
GUI -> REN : render_page_to_surface(page)
REN --> GUI : rendered page

== Impose & edit (layout-engine exists, GUI wiring planned) ==
User -> GUI : adjust N-up / booklet / rotate / reorder
GUI -[#gray]-> LAY : <<planned>> calculate() / transform()
LAY -[#gray]--> GUI : NUpLayout / BookletLayout / TransformedPage

== Submit downstream (decided, no cups dep yet) ==
User -> GUI : print to selected printer
GUI -[#gray]-> TARGET : <<planned>> submit via CUPS API
TARGET -[#gray]--> GUI : job status

note over IPC,LAY
  Grey = decided design not yet
  wired in code (Phase 1 gap)
end note
@enduml
